Note: The major version bump from 0.x - 2.x is due to the fact that this rewrite
is a port of a second generation webcpp tool for Windows.

 (g)WebcppUI
 v 2.0.1 (12/01/2006)

  - Fixed add files dialog to support multiple file selections.
  - Added descriptive tooltips.


 (g)WebcppUI
 v 2.0.0 (30/11/2005)

  - Completely redesigned GUI, completely rewritten code in python.
  - Added support for all the features you'd expect in webcpp 0.8.2 and up.
  - Added a Scs2 (Syntax Colour Scheme 2) designer for creating/editing schemes.
  - Added support for batch processing.
  - New Gtk+ 2.4 (and above) interface.


 Webcpp GnoGui
 v 0.3.3 (07/10/2002)

  - Added support for ASP, RenderMan, and Ruby.
  - Fixed Line Numbers option.
  - Webcpp 0.7.8 or later is now required.


 v 0.3.2 (03/09/2002)

  - Added support for DOS batch and VHDL.
  - Added filetype autodetect as a language option.
  - Output files now have an HTML title on them.
  - Webcpp 0.7.6 or later is now required.


 v 0.3.1 (26/07/2002)

  - Added support for Haskell, Tcl, NVidia's Cg, and NASA's CLIPS language.
  - Code cleanup inside callbacks.c.
  - Updated the about box.
  - Webcpp 0.7.3 or later is now required.


 v 0.3.0 (19/07/2002)

  - Added support for Ada95, Basic, Objective C, Fortran, Modula2, Pascal & SQL.
  - Added option Anchor Lines in place of Backup HTML.
  - Made tooltips for all the options.
  - Webcpp 0.7.2 is required.


 v 0.2.0 (05/04/2002)

  - Added Assembler, C#, and PHP to the filetype support.
  - Added "Made with" and "Tabs to spaces" options.
  - Filetypes are now using the -x=<ext> switch, -t=<ext> will phase out in later webcpp's.
  - Webcpp 0.6.8 or later is now required.


 v 0.1.0

  - Initial release.
